  "text": "As before, by solving the obtained set of equations, we have the approximating function y m(t). Table 4 shows the obtained values of y ′ (0) by the present method and comparison it with the values of Gaussian RBF (G-RBF) [CITATION_1] , rational Christov functions (RCF) [CITATION_2] , Shooting method [CITATION_3] , rational Legendre Tau method (RLT) [CITATION_4] , and exponential Legendre Tau method (ELT) [CITATION_5] for various values of b 1 and b 2 , with m = 20 and α = 0.50. Table 5 Table 7 shows the obtained values of y(t) for various values of t by the present method and comparison it with the values of Homotopy analysis method (HAM) [CITATION_6] , Gaussian RBF (G-RBF) [CITATION_7] , rational Christov functions (RCF) [CITATION_8] , rational Legendre Tau method (RLT) [CITATION_9] , and exponential Legendre Tau method (ELT) [CITATION_10] , with m = 20 and α = 0.50. ",
